-1 just for a couple of nits.

We're deleting the image upon failure of the task here (without the user ever knowing the image id?). That possibly makes it a little harder to debug what happened.

In the regular upload (PUT /v2/images/123/file) the image is not deleted, but is set back to 'queued'. I'm really not sure, but wonder if that is worth considering here? It wouldn't be possible to retry to that image id from the tasks interface, but the image id would be available to maybe help debug, and it may be possible to retry uploading the data via the standard upload API call.
